00:40:52.099 --> 00:40:59.059
I don't know about you, I've used the illustration before, but I don't want a dirty platter

00:40:59.059 --> 00:41:02.499
or a dirty utensil to just be cleaner than what it was.

00:41:02.499 --> 00:41:08.499
I want it to be clean before I use it.

00:41:08.499 --> 00:41:15.339
God wants us to be clean, not cleaner, but clean.

00:41:15.779 --> 00:41:22.059
In Acts 24, verse 16, the Bible says, and herein do I exercise myself.

00:41:22.059 --> 00:41:34.019
Notice what he says, to have always a conscience void of offense toward God and toward men.

00:41:34.019 --> 00:41:40.179
We sing the song, nothing between my soul and my Savior.

00:41:40.179 --> 00:41:43.139
Nothing between my soul and my Savior.

00:41:43.139 --> 00:41:45.259
We sing the song.

00:41:45.259 --> 00:41:50.059
And here, Paul says that he's laboring, he's striving, he's exercising.

00:41:50.059 --> 00:41:51.659
For what purpose, Paul?

00:41:51.659 --> 00:41:55.939
To have always, not to have sometimes, not to have on Sundays, not to have most times,

00:41:55.939 --> 00:42:03.099
but to have always a conscience that is void of offense toward God and toward men.

00:42:03.099 --> 00:42:05.299
Be clean.

00:42:05.299 --> 00:42:09.219
Be right with God, dealing with the sin.

00:42:09.219 --> 00:42:13.859
Because the Holy Spirit of God puts His finger on the sin in your life, in my life, that

00:42:13.859 --> 00:42:19.339
we go to God and we confess it and we forsake it and we have that forgiveness.

00:42:19.339 --> 00:42:34.499
First Corinthians 15, in verse number 34, Psalm 4 said, stand in awe and sin not.

00:42:34.499 --> 00:42:41.499
The Bible says of the children of Israel in Psalm 78 and Hosea 13, they sinned more

00:42:41.499 --> 00:42:42.499
and more.

00:42:42.499 --> 00:42:49.739
And here in First Corinthians 15, in verse 34, the Bible says, awake to righteousness

00:42:49.739 --> 00:42:51.619
and sin not.

00:42:51.619 --> 00:42:57.059
For some have not the knowledge of God, I speak this to your shame.

00:42:57.059 --> 00:43:02.379
Tonight, how do you view God?

00:43:02.379 --> 00:43:04.699
How do you view God?

00:43:04.699 --> 00:43:07.779
How did you get your view of God?

00:43:07.779 --> 00:43:08.779
Is it a biblical view?

00:43:08.779 --> 00:43:11.699
Is it an unbiblical view?

00:43:11.699 --> 00:43:15.219
Do we see Him as Isaiah, Psalm, high, holy, lifted up?

00:43:15.219 --> 00:43:20.579
Do we see Him as holy and just?

00:43:20.579 --> 00:43:22.819
How do we view our sin?

00:43:22.819 --> 00:43:26.379
Pastor, I have no sin.

00:43:26.379 --> 00:43:28.859
You've deceived yourselves.

00:43:28.859 --> 00:43:34.539
You're making God a liar, and His truth is not in you, according to 1 John 1, verse 8

00:43:34.539 --> 00:43:35.539
and verse 10.

00:43:35.539 --> 00:43:39.899
How do we view our sin?

00:43:39.899 --> 00:43:44.339
How can I do this great wickedness and sin against God?

00:43:44.339 --> 00:43:50.579
You say, well, my sin isn't fornication, my sin isn't adultery.

00:43:50.579 --> 00:43:55.859
That's what Joseph would be, that's why he calls it great wickedness.

00:43:55.859 --> 00:43:58.939
Can I remind you that Revelation 21, verse number 8 says, all liars shall have their

00:43:58.939 --> 00:44:02.739
part in the lake which burns with fire and brimstone?

00:44:02.739 --> 00:44:09.779
Can I remind you that James says that if we offend in one, that we're guilty of all?

00:44:09.779 --> 00:44:15.619
The problem is that sometimes we've gotten comfortable with, can I call them little sins

00:44:15.619 --> 00:44:18.299
tonight?

00:44:18.299 --> 00:44:23.419
I don't think they're little sins, but I'm using those quotations because sometimes that's

00:44:23.419 --> 00:44:25.739
what we've done.

00:44:25.739 --> 00:44:26.739
Everyone does it.

00:44:26.739 --> 00:44:27.899
We're comfortable with it.

00:44:27.899 --> 00:44:31.139
It's just status quo.

00:44:31.139 --> 00:44:42.579
How do we deal with it when the Holy Spirit convicts you in your own personal devotions,

00:44:42.579 --> 00:44:43.579
in a church service?

00:44:43.579 --> 00:44:46.579
Do you deal with your sin?

00:44:46.579 --> 00:44:52.219
I liked what Brother Shank said on Sunday morning two weeks ago.

00:44:52.219 --> 00:44:56.459
I talked to him after the meal and all that we did in the afternoon, and I told him how

00:44:56.459 --> 00:44:57.459
much I appreciated it.

00:44:57.459 --> 00:45:01.819
And it's just so neat to see how God orchestrates things because for two Wednesday nights leading

00:45:01.819 --> 00:45:06.219
up to that, we dealt with Exodus 9 and Exodus 16.

00:45:06.219 --> 00:45:11.899
And then he preaches, sorry, it was Exodus 9, yeah, Exodus 9 and 16, and then he preaches

00:45:11.899 --> 00:45:12.899
that message.

00:45:12.899 --> 00:45:13.899
And here's what he said.

00:45:13.899 --> 00:45:19.179
When you look in the mirror, I hope you looked at the mirror before you came to church tonight

00:45:19.179 --> 00:45:21.499
or before you went to work this morning.

00:45:21.499 --> 00:45:25.379
You look in the mirror, and if you didn't like what you saw, you didn't punch the mirror.

00:45:25.379 --> 00:45:28.299
That's what Brother Shank said.

00:45:28.299 --> 00:45:32.599
No, you fixed whatever the problem was.

00:45:32.599 --> 00:45:37.179
You addressed the issue, right?

00:45:37.179 --> 00:45:41.779
You fixed the hair, you got the thing out of your teeth because you had dinner that

00:45:41.779 --> 00:45:44.219
had herbs on it and you got stuff.

00:45:44.219 --> 00:45:46.039
You understand, right?

00:45:46.039 --> 00:45:48.539
We don't get mad at the mirror.

00:45:49.539 --> 00:45:53.099
That'd be silly.

00:45:53.099 --> 00:46:02.259
So when we look into the perfect law of liberty, the Holy Spirit of God convicts us.

00:46:02.259 --> 00:46:04.059
Don't cover it.

00:46:04.059 --> 00:46:06.419
Don't excuse it.

00:46:06.419 --> 00:46:07.419
Don't get mad.

00:46:07.419 --> 00:46:08.419
Get right.

00:46:08.419 --> 00:46:09.419
Get right.

00:46:09.419 --> 00:46:19.659
See, because carrying around that sin and getting comfortable with that sin and getting

00:46:19.659 --> 00:46:24.179
used to it is just adversely affecting your fellowship with God.

00:46:24.179 --> 00:46:30.499
And sin in the camp will affect the whole.

00:46:30.499 --> 00:46:33.139
Stand in awe and sin not.

00:46:33.139 --> 00:46:34.139
Let's pray.

00:46:34.139 --> 00:46:35.139
Father, we love you.

00:46:35.139 --> 00:46:36.439
We thank you for loving us.

00:46:36.439 --> 00:46:40.719
We thank you for your Word and the directness of it.

00:46:40.719 --> 00:46:47.599
Lord, I don't know for sure why you laid this passage of Scripture on my heart for this

00:46:47.599 --> 00:46:57.999
service this evening, but I know with confidence that this is what you want me to preach tonight.

00:46:57.999 --> 00:47:03.199
I thank you for your love.

00:47:03.199 --> 00:47:07.839
Thank you that you're a God of forgiveness.

00:47:07.839 --> 00:47:17.959
I pray, God, that you would help us to walk worthy, to walk in obedience, to walk holy.

00:47:17.959 --> 00:47:22.919
Help us to see you as we ought.

00:47:22.919 --> 00:47:31.599
Help us to see our sin as an offense, great wickedness, exceeding sinful.

00:47:31.599 --> 00:47:36.119
Help us to deal with sin biblically.

00:47:36.119 --> 00:47:39.039
Thank you for the privilege of prayer.

00:47:39.039 --> 00:47:43.719
I'm reminded even as we enter our prayer time how Samuel said, God forbid that I should

00:47:43.719 --> 00:47:49.279
sin in not praying for you.

00:47:49.279 --> 00:47:58.759
Something that probably most of us never would think of as being sin.

00:47:58.919 --> 00:48:03.079
Help us to walk worthy.

00:48:03.079 --> 00:48:10.439
Thank you for what you'll do for us in Christ's name we pray, amen.

